Celebrities will be ferried in a Guinness Smooth branded plane to Kisumu for the launch of the brand new stout. The event will take place on Saturday. Artists set to perform include Willy Paul, Khaligraph Jones and Sailors. Comedians Jalango and Otoyo will also grace the event. DJs Bash, Joe Mfalme and Pharee will be on the decks. Guinness Smooth, the latest addition to the Guinness family, is said to be uniquely smooth and has a refreshing taste. The star-studded event will take place at the Simba Union Club. The plane leave for Kisumu from the Jomo Kenyatta International Airport. The only time Kenyan celebs hire planes is to land for award shows or attend ceremonies such as weddings.